result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Devan L. Geboy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).
  • Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: The defendant shall not commit any criminal offenses; shall notify the Taylor County District Attorney's Office, as well as the Clerk of Court's office, of any change of address within ten days of said change. Defendant shall engage in and actively participate in counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.  Defendant shall obtain/maintain full time employment at the discretion of probation.
Defendant must undergo an AODA and all recommended follow through treatment.  Proof of assessment must be provided to the district attorney's office.

judgments.dispoDesc: Pursuant to an agreement and on motion of the State, the court granted a deferred entry of judgment for a period of two years.  Upon successful completion of the agreement, the state will move to dismiss the felony charge.

miscConds.notes:
Defendant shall submit to a DNA sample at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department.  Defendant shall undergo counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.  Defendant shall obtain/maintain full time employment at the discretion of probation.    Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. 
If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA and follow through with any recommendations.

timeConds.notes:
The jail sentence shall begin no later than February 6, 2017 at 4:30 pm.  The jail sentence may be served with good time.  The defendant shall pay all sheriff and jail fees or costs allowed or imposed by law and the sheriff shall be entitled to a judgment against the defendant for any such unpaid fees or costs.  
Jail can be served in any county in the State of Wisconsin provided arrangements are made by counsel or the defendant, it is approved by the Taylor County Jail, and at no additional cost to Taylor County.

Written Waiver of Preliminary Examination

Defendant Devan L. Geboy in court with attorney Shawn M Paul.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court questions defendant regarding a preliminary hearing.  Defendant freely and voluntarily waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  A written waiver was filed with the court.  Information filed.  Waive reading of Information.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to counts 1, 2 and 3.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty of counts 1, 2 and 3.  Statement by Attorney Tlusty and Attorney Paul.  Court defers entry of judgment on Count 1 for a period of one year with conditions of AODA ;  counseling as deemed appropriate by probation; obtain/maintain full time employment at the discretion of probation; successfully complete probation for counts 2 and 3.  Court orders in Counts 2 and 3 - withheld sentence with two years probation with conditions of court costs on each count; submit to a DNA sample and surcharge on count 2; AODA; counseling as deemed appropriate by probation; obtain/maintain full time employment at discretion of the probation agent; 30 days county jail with huber on each count concurrent to each other to begin no later than February 6, 2017 at 4:30 pm.  - rt
